Minister Zweli Mkhize confirms total of 607 045 cases of Coronavirus COVID-19 As of today, a cumulative total of 607 045 confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa have been recorded with 3 707 new cases identified. Case Data Province Total cases for 21 August 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 85039 14,0 Free State 34621 5,7 Gauteng 205246 33,8 KwaZulu-Natal 109332 18,0 Limpopo 12389 2,0 Mpumalanga 22902 3,8 North West 24185 4,0 Northern Cape 8996 1,5 Western Cape 104285 17,2 Unknown 50 0,0 Total 607045 100,0 Testing Data The total number of tests conducted to date is 3 535 067 with 30 560 new tests conducted since the last report. Reported Deaths and Recoveries Regrettably we report a further 144 COVID-19 related deaths- 25 from Eastern Cape, 37 from Gauteng, 46 from Mpumalanga, 31 from KwaZulu-Natal, and 5 from Western Cape. This brings the total COVID-19 related cumulative deaths to 12 987 We convey our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers who treated the deceased. The recoveries now stand at 504 127 which translates to a recovery rate of 83% Province Deaths Recoveries Active cases Eastern Cape 2778 80614 1647 Free State 567 20641 13413 Gauteng 3227 171839 30180 KwaZulu-Natal 1936 84530 22866 Limpopo 171 10559 1659 Mpumalanga 260 20254 2388 North West 224 17007 6954 Northern Cape 106 5300 3590 Western Cape 3718 93383 7184 Total 12987 504127 89881 UPDATE: 21 August 2020 As of today, a cumulative total of 603 338 confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa have been recorded with 3 398 new cases identified. Case Data Province Total cases for 21 August 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 84787 14,1 Free State 34136 5,7 Gauteng 203832 33,8 KwaZulu-Natal 108788 18,0 Limpopo 12281 2,0 Mpumalanga 22701 3,8 North West 24003 4,0 Northern Cape 8818 1,5 Western Cape 103942 17,2 Unknown 50 0,0 Total 603338 100,0 Testing Data The total number of tests conducted to date is 3 504 507 with 24 224 new tests conducted since the last report Rep